title: Three Hundred Tang Poems, Volume 3
creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Three Hundred Tang Poems, Volume 3, in the public domain.
The LibriVox catalog page for this work lists the authors, the titles in English and the LibriVox readers. There are also links to the texts in Chinese and English. Compiled around 1763, 'Three Hundred Tang Poems' is the standard collection of the poetic art of the Tang Dynasty (618 to 907). Poems in Volume Three are of the style 五言律詩 'five character regular verse' (poems 90 to 169). (Summary by David Barnes) For more information on LibriVox, or to volunteer, please see: http://librivox.org/
M4B format available
